cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with enhancing low-light images using computer vision techniques, which falls under the purview of this sub-category.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image enhancement, which is a key aspect of multimedia processing.
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with image synthesis and fusion, which is a key aspect of computer graphics.
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper mentions the human visual system and how it inspired the proposed framework, which falls under the purview of this sub-category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions the camera response model and how it is used to synthesize multi-exposure images, which falls under the purview of this sub-category.
